What you need to know:

The Magical Kenya Open is set for March 18 to 21 at Karen Country Club, while the Kenya Savannah Classic follows from March 23 to 26 at the same venueRadier said that supporting and leveraging on sports is one of the long-term strategies that KTB is looking at to boost the country’s tourism sectorRadier noted that the addition of the Kenya Savannah Classic to this year’s list of the European Tour events is testament to the growing status of golf in the country, further adding that the events will increase confidence in the destination to travellers